TITLE: Nordstrom earnings top expectations as retailer starts winding down Canada operations
SUMMARY: Nordstrom has struggled with slower sales, more markdowns and pressure from activist investor Ryan Cohen.

TITLE: Best Buy tops holiday-quarter expectations but warns of further sales declines in the coming year
SUMMARY: Best Buy posted earnings and revenue that beat analysts' estimates for its holiday quarter.

TITLE: Macy's shares jump after holiday-quarter profit tops expectations
SUMMARY: Macy's delivered a bigger profit than expected during the holiday quarter.

TITLE: Polestar cuts annual losses in half as it ramps up EV production
SUMMARY: Polestar's relatively positive results come after other EV startups like Lucid, Nikola and Rivian reported ongoing problems with supply chains and production.

TITLE: Salesforce shares jump 16% on better-than-expected forecast
SUMMARY: Salesforce shares surged in extended trading on Wednesday on an optimistic earnings outlook.

TITLE: Kohl's posts surprising holiday-quarter loss, offers weak sales outlook
SUMMARY: Kohl's sales for the holiday quarter came in well below Wall Street's expectations.

TITLE: Lowe's offers soft sales outlook, warning of a 'cautious consumer'
SUMMARY: Lowe's issued a conservative outlook for the next fiscal year as the home improvement sector faces pressure from a shift in consumer spending.

TITLE: Rivian posts mixed fourth quarter and underwhelming EV production outlook, stock falls
SUMMARY: The results follow slower-than-expected production, unexpected pricing pressure and plans to lay off 6% of its workforce in a bid to conserve cash.

TITLE: Virgin Galactic completes lengthy upgrade process ahead of resuming spaceflights
SUMMARY: Virgin Galactic reported fourth-quarter results on Tuesday, with the company saying it remains on track to resume spaceflights in the coming months.

TITLE: Rocket Lab quarterly revenue stays steady as space company doubles order backlog
SUMMARY: Rocket Lab said Tuesday it has doubled its order backlog â€” from about $241 million in contracts at the end of 2021 to $503.6 million at the end of 2022.

TITLE: Norwegian Cruise Line shares fall 10% as soft outlook, wider losses eclipse strong demand
SUMMARY: Norwegian Cruise Line's stock fell as high costs and debt weigh on the company even as travel demand has stayed strong.

TITLE: Target ekes out slight growth in holiday-quarter sales, but warns of continued slowdown
SUMMARY: CEO Brian Cornell in a release cited "a very challenging environment," with groceries, beauty items and household essentials lifting sales as consumers focused on necessities.

TITLE: Zoom shares jump on better-than-expected fourth-quarter results
SUMMARY: While Zoom's earnings guidance was better than expected, the company continues to see a dramatic slowdown in growth from the Covid boom.

TITLE: Block misses on earnings but beats on revenue, gross profit
SUMMARY: Block stock rose slightly in extended trading after the payments company reported fourth-quarter revenue and gross profit that beat Wall Street's expectations.

TITLE: Warner Bros Discovery revenue misses as media giant posts big loss
SUMMARY: Warner Bros. Discovery reported its fourth quarter results after the bell.

TITLE: Beyond Meat reports narrow-than-expected quarterly loss despite sinking sales
SUMMARY: Beyond Meat said its sales could fall as much as 10% in 2023.

TITLE: Moderna misses on earnings as costs rise from surplus production capacity, lower Covid shot demand
SUMMARY: Moderna reported quarterly earnings of $3.61 per share, a 68% decrease from the same period in 2021 when it booked $11.29 per share.

TITLE: Alibaba shares rally 6% after massive earnings beat
SUMMARY: Alibaba reported earnings for its fiscal third quarter that smashed expectations, sending shares soaring 6% higher.

TITLE: Qantas is confident it will return to 100% of its pre-Covid capacity in 2024
SUMMARY: Qantas is confident that it will see a full return to pre-Covid capacity in 2024, CEO Alan Joyce told CNBC.

TITLE: Nvidia stock rises after slight beat driven by A.I. chips
SUMMARY: Nvidia has increasingly been seen by investors as one of the chip stocks best positioned to endure an economic slowdown that hurts PC and semiconductor sales.

TITLE: Lucid's revenue falls short of estimates as it guides to higher EV production in 2023
SUMMARY: Lucid built just 7,000 of its Air luxury sedans last year amid manufacturing challenges but expects to make between 10,000 and 14,000 vehicles in 2023.

TITLE: Jeep, Dodge maker Stellantis posts record annual profit, announces $4.47 billion shareholder payout
SUMMARY: Carmaker Stellantis on Wednesday announced record full-year results, reporting a 26% rise in net profit to 16.8 billion euros ($17.9 billion) and a 41% annual jump in global battery and electric vehicle sales.

TITLE: Coinbase beats on revenue and earnings, but usage continues to decline
SUMMARY: Coinbase beats on revenue and earnings, but usage continues to decline

TITLE: Palo Alto Networks lifts earnings guidance as it pursues profitable growth
SUMMARY: Palo Alto Networks is emphasizing profitability while still adding top-line growth through acquisitions under CEO Nikesh Arora.

TITLE: Walmart gives soft outlook for the year after posting strong holiday quarter
SUMMARY: Walmart gave a weaker-than-expected outlook for the year ahead.

TITLE: Home Depot misses revenue expectations for the first time since 2019
SUMMARY: Home Depot fell short of Wall Street's sales estimates due to a drop in lumber prices and provided a muted outlook for the next fiscal year.

TITLE: HSBC reports fourth-quarter pre-tax profit of $5.2 billion, beating estimates
SUMMARY: The bank said its fourth-quarter results reflect strong reported revenue growth and lower reported operating expenses.

TITLE: DoorDash stock pops after revenue beat, rosy guidance
SUMMARY: DoorDash reported better-than-expected sales for the fourth quarter and gave upbeat guidance for the current period.

TITLE: Hasbro keeps expectations low for the start of 2023, but sees turnaround coming
SUMMARY: Hasbro reported disappointing holiday sales, which it had anticipated given slowing consumer demand.

TITLE: Paramount+ plans price increases as it hits 56 million subscribers
SUMMARY: Paramount Global reported 9.9 million in streaming subscriber additions. The company plans price increases this year.
